Terraform: 
Its a open source tool for infrastructure provisioning & Deploying Application . Its written in a language called HASHEY CORP CONFIGURATION LANGUAGE.
Working on the principle of IaC
Automate and manage your infrastructure and services that run on the platform

Architecture:
1. Provider : Allow us to communicate with specific set of APIs ( AWS , AZURE , GCP )
provider "aws" {
  region = " "
  access_key = " "
  secret_key = " "
  }
2. Core
Tf-Config - What needs to create and configure
Tf-State - Up to date state of the current setup

Stages :
Terraform Init --> Tarraform plan --> Terraform apply ( Click " YES " )

Basic Commands:
1. Refresh  - Query the Infrastaructure provider to get Current state
2. Plan - Create a Execution plan like PREVIEW
3. Apply - Execute the Plan like to get a OUTPUT
4. Destroy - Delete the Resource infrastructure
5. State Lise - Listout all the resources 
6. State show - Datail about the resources 

Terraform Files:
1. Provider Plugins File
2. Terraform .tf state file 
3. Terraform .tf state backup


